authorizationSystems.description: Represents an onboarded AWS account, Azure subscription, or GCP project that Microsoft Entra Permissions Management will collect and analyze permissions and actions on.

authorizationSystemId.description: ID of the authorization system retrieved from the customer cloud environment. Supports $filter(eq, contains) and $orderBy.

authorizationSystemName.description: Name of the authorization system detected after onboarding. Supports $filter(eq,contains) and $orderBy.

authorizationSystemType.description: The type of authorization system. Can be gcp, azure, or aws. Supports $filter(eq).

description.description: Description of the connection displayed in the Microsoft 365 admin center. Optional.

ingestedItemsCount.description: The number of items ingested into a connection. This value is refreshed every 15 minutes. If the connection state is draft, then ingestedItemsCount will be null.

name.description: The display name of the connection to be displayed in the Microsoft 365 admin center. Maximum length of 128 characters. Required.

description.description: The description of the external group. Optional.

displayName.description: The friendly name of the external group. Optional.

members.description: A member added to an externalGroup. You can add Microsoft Entra users, Microsoft Entra groups, or other externalGroups as members.

acl.description: An array of access control entries. Each entry specifies the access granted to a user or group. Required.

activities.description: Returns a list of activities performed on the item. Write-only.

startDateTime.description: The date and time when the particular activity occurred. The DateTimeOffset type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

itemsRemaining.description: The minimum of two values, one representing the items remaining in the connection and the other remaining items at tenant-level. The following equation represents the formula used to calculate the minimum number: min ({max capacity in the connection} – {number of items in the connection}, {tenant quota} – {number of items indexed in all connections}). If the connection is not monetized, such as in a preview connector or preview content experience, then this property is simply the number of remaining items in the connection.

baseType.description: Must be set to microsoft.graph.externalItem. Required.

properties.description: The properties defined for the items in the connection. The minimum number of properties is one, the maximum is 128.

dataConnectors.description: Set of connectors for importing data from source systems.

inboundFlows.description: Set of data import flow activities to bring data into the canonical store via a connector.

operations.description: Set of ephemeral operations that the system runs currently. Read-only.

referenceDefinitions.description: Set of user modifiable system picker types.

roleGroups.description: Set of groups of individual roles that makes role-based admin simpler.

runs.description: Set of ephemeral runs which present the point-in-time that diagnostic state of activities performed by the system. Read-only.

sourceSystems.description: Set of source definitions that represents real-world external systems.

years.description: Set of years represented in the system.

displayName.description: The name of the data connector. Maximum supported length is 100 characters.
The name of the source system. Maximum supported length is 100 characters.

userMatchingSettings.description: A collection of user matching settings by roleGroup.

vendor.description: The name of the vendor who supplies the source system. Maximum supported length is 100 characters.

effectiveDateTime.description: The start of the time window when the flow is allowed to run. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

expirationDateTime.description: The end of the time window when the flow is allowed to run. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

displayName.description: The name of the year. Maximum supported length is 100 characters.

endDate.description: The last day of the year using ISO 8601 format for date.

startDate.description: The first day of the year using ISO 8601 format for date.

createdDateTime.description: The start time of the operation. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

lastActionDateTime.description: The time of the last action in the operation. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

resourceLocation.description: URI of the resource that the operation is performed on.

statusDetail.description: Details about the status of the operation.

createdDateTime.description: The date and time when the flowSet was created. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

displayName.description: The display name of the flowSet provided by the caller.

lastModifiedDateTime.description: The date and time when the flowSet was most recently changed. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

provisioningFlows.description: A flow that provisions relevant records of a given entity type in the Microsoft 365 tenant.

createdDateTime.description: The date and time when the provisioning flow was created. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

lastModifiedDateTime.description: The date and time when the provisioning flow was most recently changed. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

code.description: The code value for the definition that must be unique within the referenceType.

createdDateTime.description: The date and time when the definition was created. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

displayName.description: A human-readable representation of the reference code value for display in a user interface.

isDisabled.description: Indicates whether the definition is disabled.

lastModifiedDateTime.description: The date and time when the definition was most recently changed. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

referenceType.description: The categorical type for a collection of enumerated values.

sortIndex.description: The index that specifies the order in which to present the definition to the user. Must be unique within the referenceType.

source.description: The standards body or organization source which defined the code.

displayName.description: The name of the role group.

roles.description: The set of roles included in the role group.

displayName.description: The name of the run for rendering in a user interface.

endDateTime.description: The date and time when the run finished or null if the run is still in-progress. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

startDateTime.description: The date and time when the run started. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

activities.description: The set of activities performed during the run.

displayName.description: The name of the running flow.
The name of the activity. Maximum supported length is 100 characters.

activityStatistics.description: The collection of statistics for each activity included in this run.

runId.description: The ID of the underlying run for the statistics.

acronyms.description: Administrative answer in Microsoft Search results to define common acronyms in an organization.

bookmarks.description: Administrative answer in Microsoft Search results for common search queries in an organization.

qnas.description: Administrative answer in Microsoft Search results that provide answers for specific search keywords in an organization.

availabilityEndDateTime.description: Date and time when the bookmark stops appearing as a search result. Set as null for always available. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

availabilityStartDateTime.description: Date and time when the bookmark starts to appear as a search result. Set as null for always available. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

categories.description: Categories commonly used to describe this bookmark. For example, IT and HR.

groupIds.description: The list of security groups that are able to view this bookmark.

isSuggested.description: True if this bookmark was suggested to the admin, by a user, or was mined and suggested by Microsoft. Read-only.

languageTags.description: A list of geographically specific language names in which this bookmark can be viewed. Each language tag value follows the pattern {language}-{region}. For example, en-us is English as used in the United States. For the list of possible values, see Supported language tags.

platforms.description: List of devices and operating systems that are able to view this bookmark. Possible values are: android, androidForWork, ios, macOS, windowsPhone81, windowsPhone81AndLater, windows10AndLater, androidWorkProfile, unknown, androidASOP, androidMobileApplicationManagement, iOSMobileApplicationManagement, unknownFutureValue.

powerAppIds.description: List of Power Apps associated with this bookmark. If users add existing Power Apps to a bookmark, they can complete tasks directly on the search results page, such as entering vacation time or reporting expenses.

targetedVariations.description: Variations of a bookmark for different countries or devices. Use when you need to show different content to users based on their device, country/region, or both. The date and group settings apply to all variations.

aggregationFilters.description: Contains one or more filters to obtain search results aggregated and filtered to a specific value of a field. Optional.Build this filter based on a prior search that aggregates by the same field. From the response of the prior search, identify the searchBucket that filters results to the specific value of the field, use the string in its aggregationFilterToken property, and build an aggregation filter string in the format '{field}:/'{aggregationFilterToken}/''. If multiple values for the same field need to be provided, use the strings in its aggregationFilterToken property and build an aggregation filter string in the format '{field}:or(/'{aggregationFilterToken1}/',/'{aggregationFilterToken2}/')'. For example, searching and aggregating drive items by file type returns a searchBucket for the file type docx in the response. You can conveniently use the aggregationFilterToken returned for this searchBucket in a subsequent search query and filter matches down to drive items of the docx file type. Example 1 and example 2 show the actual requests and responses.

aggregations.description: Specifies aggregations (also known as refiners) to be returned alongside search results. Optional.

collapseProperties.description: Contains the ordered collection of fields and limit to collapse results. Optional.

contentSources.description: Contains the connection to be targeted. Respects the following format : /external/connections/connectionid where connectionid is the ConnectionId defined in the Connectors Administration.  Note: contentSource is only applicable when entityType=externalItem. Optional.

enableTopResults.description: This triggers hybrid sort for messages: the first 3 messages are the most relevant. This property is only applicable to entityType=message. Optional.

entityTypes.description: One or more types of resources expected in the response. Possible values are: list, site, listItem, message, event, drive, driveItem, person, externalItem, acronym, bookmark, chatMessage. For details about combinations of two or more entity types that are supported in the same search request, see known limitations. Required.

fields.description: Contains the fields to be returned for each resource object specified in entityTypes, allowing customization of the fields returned by default otherwise, including additional fields such as custom managed properties from SharePoint and OneDrive, or custom fields in externalItem from content that Microsoft Graph connectors bring in. The fields property can be using the semantic labels applied to properties. For example, if a property is label as title, you can retrieve it using the following syntax : label_title.Optional.

from.description: Specifies the offset for the search results. Offset 0 returns the very first result. Optional.

region.description: Required for searches that use application permissions. Represents the geographic location for the search. For details, see Get the region value.

size.description: The size of the page to be retrieved. The maximum value is 500. Optional.

sortProperties.description: Contains the ordered collection of fields and direction to sort results. There can be at most 5 sort properties in the collection. Optional.

stored_fields.description: This is now replaced by the fields property.

trimDuplicates.description: Indicates whether to trim away the duplicate SharePoint files from search results. Default value is false. Optional.

searchTerms.description: Contains the search terms sent in the initial search query.

availabilityEndDateTime.description: Date and time when the QnA stops appearing as a search result. Set as null for always available. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

availabilityStartDateTime.description: Date and time when the QnA starts to appear as a search result. Set as null for always available. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

groupIds.description: The list of security groups that are able to view this QnA.

isSuggested.description: True if a user or Microsoft suggested this QnA to the admin. Read-only.

languageTags.description: A list of geographically specific language names in which this QnA can be viewed. Each language tag value follows the pattern {language}-{region}. For example, en-us is English as used in the United States. For the list of possible values, see Supported language tags.

platforms.description: List of devices and operating systems that are able to view this QnA. Possible values are: android, androidForWork, ios, macOS, windowsPhone81, windowsPhone81AndLater, windows10AndLater, androidWorkProfile, unknown, androidASOP, androidMobileApplicationManagement, iOSMobileApplicationManagement, unknownFutureValue.

targetedVariations.description: Variations of a QnA for different countries or devices. Use when you need to show different content to users based on their device, country/region, or both. The date and group settings apply to all variations.

id.description: The unique identifier for an entity. Read-only.

urlToItemResolvers.description: Specifies configurations to identify an externalItem based on a shared URL.

authorizedAppIds.description: A collection of application IDs for registered Microsoft Entra apps that are allowed to manage the externalConnection and to index content in the externalConnection.

searchResultTemplates.description: Enables the developer to define the appearance of the content and configure conditions that dictate when the template should be displayed. Maximum of 2 search result templates per connection.

value.description: The unique identifer of the identity. For Microsoft Entra identities, value is set to the object identifier of the user, group or tenant for types user, group and everyone (and everyoneExceptGuests) respectively. For external groups, value is set to the ID of the externalGroup.
The content for the externalItem. Required.

message.description: A non-localized message for the developer.

aliases.description: A set of aliases or friendly names for the property. Maximum 32 characters. Only alphanumeric characters allowed. For example, each string might not contain control characters, whitespace, or any of the following: :, ;, ,, (, ), [, ], {, }, %, $, +, !, *, =, &, ?, @, #, /, ~, ', ', <, >, `, ^. Optional.

isExactMatchRequired.description: Specifies if the property will be matched exactly for queries. Exact matching can only be set to true for non-searchable properties of type string or stringCollection. Optional.

isQueryable.description: Specifies if the property is queryable. Queryable properties can be used in Keyword Query Language (KQL) queries. Optional.

isRefinable.description: Specifies if the property is refinable.  Refinable properties can be used to filter search results in the Search API and add a refiner control in the Microsoft Search user experience. Optional.

isRetrievable.description: Specifies if the property is retrievable. Retrievable properties are returned in the result set when items are returned by the search API. Retrievable properties are also available to add to the display template used to render search results. Optional.

isSearchable.description: Specifies if the property is searchable. Only properties of type string or stringCollection can be searchable. Non-searchable properties aren't added to the search index. Optional.

labels.description: Specifies one or more well-known tags added against a property. Labels help Microsoft Search understand the semantics of the data in the connection. Adding appropriate labels would result in an enhanced search experience (for example, better relevance). Optional.The possible values are: title, url, createdBy, lastModifiedBy, authors, createdDateTime, lastModifiedDateTime, fileName, fileExtension, unknownFutureValue, containerName, containerUrl, iconUrl. You must use the Prefer: include-unknown-enum-members request header to get the following values in this evolvable enum: containerName, containerUrl, iconUrl.

name.description: The name of the property. Maximum 32 characters. Only alphanumeric characters allowed. For example, the property name may not contain control characters, whitespace, or any of the following: :, ;, ,, (, ), [, ], {, }, %, $, +, !, *, =, &, ?, @, #, /, ~, ', ', <, >, `, ^.  Required.

priorityOrder.description: The priority order to apply when a user has multiple RefRole codes assigned.

activityId.description: The identifier for the activity that is being reported on.

displayName.description: The display name of the underlying flow.

errors.description: The aggregate count of errors encountered by activities during this run.

groups.description: The aggregate count of active inbound groups processed during the run.

matchedPeopleByRole.description: The aggregate count of active people matched to a Microsoft Entra user, by role.

memberships.description: The aggregate count of active inbound memberships processed during the run.

organizations.description: The aggregate count of active inbound organizations processed during the run.

people.description: The aggregate count of active inbound people processed during the run.

unmatchedPeopleByRole.description: The aggregate count of active people not matched to a Microsoft Entra user, by role.

warnings.description: The aggregate count of warnings generated by activities during this run.

description.description: The search answer description that is shown on the search results page.

displayName.description: The search answer name that is displayed in search results.

lastModifiedDateTime.description: Date and time when the search answer was created or last edited. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z. Read-only.

webUrl.description: The URL link for the search answer. When users select this search answer from the search results, they're directed to the specified URL.

keywords.description: A collection of keywords used to trigger the search answer.

matchSimilarKeywords.description: If true, indicates that the search term contains similar words to the keywords that should trigger the search answer.

reservedKeywords.description: Unique keywords that guarantee the search answer is triggered.

values.description: Indicates Mobile Application Management (MAM) for android devices.
values.name: androidMobileApplicationManagement

values.description: Indicates Mobile Application Management (MAM) for iOS devices
values.name: iOSMobileApplicationManagement

values.description: Evolvable enumeration sentinel value. Do not use
values.name: unknownFutureValue

values.description: Indicates Mobile Application Management (MAM) for Windows devices.
values.name: windowsMobileApplicationManagement

description.description: The answer variation description that is shown on the search results page.

displayName.description: The answer variation name that is displayed in search results.

languageTag.description: The country or region that can view this answer variation.

webUrl.description: The URL link for the answer variation. When users select this answer variation from the search results, they're directed to the specified URL.

field.description: Computes aggregation on the field while the field exists in the current entity type. Required.

size.description: The number of searchBucket resources to be returned. This isn't required when the range is provided manually in the search request. The minimum accepted size is 1, and the maximum is 65535. Optional.

fields.description: Defines the collapse group to trim results. The properties in this collection must be sortable/refinable properties. Required.

limit.description: Defines a maximum limit count for this field. This numeric value must be a positive integer. Required.

queryString.description: The search query containing the search terms. Required.

queryTemplate.description: Provides a way to decorate the query string. Supports both KQL and query variables. Optional.

enableModification.description: Indicates whether spelling modifications are enabled. If enabled, user will get the search results for corrected query when there are no results for the original query with typos and get the spelling modification information in queryAlterationResponse property of the response. Optional.

enableSuggestion.description: Indicates whether spelling suggestions are enabled. If enabled, the user will get the search results for the original search query and suggestions for spelling correction in the queryAlterationResponse property of the response for the typos in the query. Optional.

enableResultTemplate.description: Indicates whether search display layouts are enabled. If enabled, the user will get the result template to render the search results content in the resultTemplates property of the response. The result template is based on Adaptive Cards. This property is optional.

isDescending.description: True if the sort order is descending. Default is false, with the sort order as ascending. Optional.

name.description: The name of the property to sort on. Required.

aggregations.description: Contains the collection of aggregations computed based on the provided aggregationOption specified in the request.

hits.description: A collection of the search results.

moreResultsAvailable.description: Provides information if more results are available. Based on this information, you can adjust the from and size properties of the searchRequest accordingly.

total.description: The total number of results. Note this is not the number of results on the page, but the total number of results satisfying the query.

originalQueryString.description: Defines the original user query string.

priority.description: The priority which defines the sequence in which the urlToItemResolverBase instances are evaluated.

id.description: The text identifier for the display template; for example, contosoTickets. Maximum 16 characters. Only alphanumeric characters allowed.

priority.description: Defines the priority of a display template. A display template with priority 1 is evaluated before a template with priority 4. Gaps in priority values are supported. Must be positive value.

rules.description: Specifies additional rules for selecting this display template based on the item schema. Optional.

code.description: The code of the desired referenceDefinition entry.

count.description: The number of people in this role.

role.description: The role that is being measured.

isDescending.description: True to specify the sort order as descending. The default is false, with the sort order as ascending. Optional.

minimumCount.description: The minimum number of items that should be present in the aggregation to be returned in a bucket. Optional.

prefixFilter.description: A filter to define a matching criteria. The key should start with the specified prefix to be returned in the response. Optional.

ranges.description: Specifies the manual ranges to compute the aggregations. This is only valid for nonstring refiners of date or numeric type. Optional.

buckets.description: Defines the actual buckets of the computed aggregation.

field.description: Defines on which field the aggregation was computed on.

contentSource.description: The name of the content source that the externalItem is part of.

hitId.description: The internal identifier for the item. The format of the identifier varies based on the entity type. For details, see hitId format.

isCollapsed.description: Indicates whether the current result is collapses when the collapseProperties property in the searchRequest is used.

rank.description: The rank or the order of the result.

resultTemplateId.description: ID of the result template for rendering the search result. This ID must map to a display layout in the resultTemplates dictionary, included in the searchresponse as well.

summary.description: A summary of the result, if a summary is available.

alteredHighlightedQueryString.description: Defines the altered highlighted query string with spelling correction. The annotation around the corrected segment is (/ue000, /ue001)

alteredQueryString.description: Defines the altered query string with spelling correction.

alteredQueryTokens.description: Represents changed segments with respect to original query.

property.description: The property from the externalItem schema. Required.

values.description: A collection with one or many strings. One or more specified strings are matched with the specified property using the specified operation. Required.

from.description: Defines the lower bound from which to compute the aggregation. This can be a numeric value or a string representation of a date using the YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss.sssZ format. Required.

to.description: Defines the upper bound up to which to compute the aggregation. This can be a numeric value or a string representation of a date using the YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss.sssZ format. Required.

aggregationFilterToken.description: A token containing the encoded filter to aggregate search matches by the specific key value. To use the filter, pass the token as part of the aggregationFilter property in a searchRequest object, in the format '{field}:/'{aggregationFilterToken}/''. See an example.

count.description: The approximate number of search matches that share the same value specified in the key property. Note that this number is not the exact number of matches.

key.description: The discrete value of the field that an aggregation was computed on.

length.description: Defines the length of a changed segment.

offset.description: Defines the offset of a changed segment.
